{
  "texts": [
    "These tests establish the statistical detectability of each predictor's association with disclosure behavior.",
    "Wald tests were chosen over likelihood ratio tests because the experiment includes non-independent observations, and Wald tests with clustered standard errors correctly account for this.Test 3 (Rank Correlation): Finally, Spearman's rank correlation [37], 𝜌, was computed between model-level disclosure rates and the logarithm of the parameter count.",
    "Disclosure rates were aggregated across all conversations by tested large language model (n=16 models) before calculating the correlation.",
    "This test assesses whether larger models systematically achieve higher disclosure rates.",
    "Results Substantial Model Heterogeneity in Self-TransparencyModels demonstrate near-perfect self-transparency under baseline conditions, disclosing their AI nature in 99.8-99.9% of interactions when assigned no persona or an explicit AI assistant identity."
  ]
}